":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."]}]},{"name":"Angharad","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old Celtic intensive prefix <i>an-</i> + <i>cār</i> ‘love’ + the noun suffix <i>-ad</i>. This was the name of the mother of the 12th-century chronicler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad Gruffudd was born in 1380, in Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Gruffudd Ap Rhys, was 50 and her mother, Efa Einion, was 51. She had at least 1 daughter with Jenkyn Lloyd Ap Rhys."},"et":{"1380–":"1380–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1376–Male":"1376–Surnud","1422–1530":"1422–1530","–Male":"Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1329–Female":"1329–Surnud","1422":"1422","1530":"1530","1376":"1376","1330":"1330","1380":"1380","1329":"1329","Pwildyfarch, Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1380–":"1380–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1376–Male":"1376–Kuollut","1422–1530":"1422–1530","–Male":"Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1329–Female":"1329–Kuollut","1422":"1422","1530":"1530","1376":"1376","1330":"1330","1380":"1380","1329":"1329","Pwildyfarch, Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1380–":"1380–Décédée","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","1376–Male":"1376–Décédé","1422–1530":"1422–1530","–Male":"Décédé","